data.text:
July 16, 1939 was a Sunday and it was the 197th day of the year 1939 in the Gregorian calendar.

July 16, 1939 can also be written as 7/16/1939 in the US and as 16/7/1939 in UK and Europe.

Moon phase

The moon phase on July 16, 1939 was New Moon.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on July 16, 1939 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on July 16, 1939 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 2% full, rising at 05:26 am and setting at 08:48 pm.

The previous full moon was on Jul 01, 1939 while the next full moon would come on Jul 31, 1939.

What is special about July 16th?

July 16th refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 16th day of the month of July. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.

Over the years several events happened on July 16th, such as:

2019 - Syrian civil war: airstrikes by the syrian government targeting residential areas in jisr al-shughur and khan shaykhun in idlib province kill at least nine civilians, and injure fourteen others.

2018 - 2015-2018 iraqi protests - demonstrations in iraq leave many people dead and create mass unrest.

2017 - Jodie whittaker will replace peter capaldi in the 13th doctor's incarnation, making her the first woman to assume the role of doctor who's science fiction television series.
